  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-12-11",
    "date": "2020-03-05T16:20:18Z",
    "text": "Safety is Not for Sale Act of 2019 \n\nThis bill directs the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to require aircraft manufacturers to offer or provide non-required safety enhancing equipment without an additional charge to an air carrier.\n\nThe FAA must implement a program to identify, classify, and approve certain non-required safety enhancing equipment.\n\nThe FAA must also establish performance standards for aircraft angle of attack indicators, disagree alerts, and backup fire suppressions systems."
  },
